cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with learning 2D image embeddings with a 3D equivariant structure, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves learning embeddings using a neural network, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with geometric properties of images, which could fall under cs.GR (Computer Graphics). The paper involves supervised learning, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves novel view synthesis, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
